00:04:32.120 --> 00:04:35.060 align:middle line:84%
the day or, you know,
just to function normally.

00:04:35.060 --> 00:04:39.900 align:middle line:84%
Even just the normal day to day
tasks were an effort for you.

00:04:39.900 --> 00:04:40.700 align:middle line:90%
>> I didn't--

00:04:40.700 --> 00:04:42.470 align:middle line:90%
I went through a stage, where--

00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:46.970 align:middle line:84%
we live in a beautiful area, and
my son had just started school.

00:04:46.970 --> 00:04:49.760 align:middle line:84%
So I was in this
position for four years.

00:04:49.760 --> 00:04:51.470 align:middle line:84%
I didn't snap out of
it for four years.

00:04:51.470 --> 00:04:54.530 align:middle line:84%
And then my son
started getting invited

00:04:54.530 --> 00:04:57.695 align:middle line:84%
to all these
beautiful homes, and I

00:04:57.695 --> 00:04:58.820 align:middle line:90%
went to go and pick him up.

00:04:58.820 --> 00:05:00.410 align:middle line:84%
And then he'd always
say to me, Mommy,

00:05:00.410 --> 00:05:02.480 align:middle line:84%
can people come and
play at our house?

00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:05.810 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say no, because
I was too embarrassed

00:05:05.810 --> 00:05:07.190 align:middle line:90%
to bring people there.

00:05:07.190 --> 00:05:10.740 align:middle line:84%
And that just made it get deeper
and deeper, spiraling down.

00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:13.190 align:middle line:84%
What sort of mom am I
to not let people come

00:05:13.190 --> 00:05:15.200 align:middle line:90%
and play with their children?

00:05:15.200 --> 00:05:19.230 align:middle line:84%
So it all just became
about this whole life

00:05:19.230 --> 00:05:22.320 align:middle line:84%
I had created that I
was too embarrassed

00:05:22.320 --> 00:05:24.090 align:middle line:90%
to share with the world.

00:05:24.090 --> 00:05:26.340 align:middle line:90%
So that just made it worse.

00:05:26.340 --> 00:05:28.740 align:middle line:84%
>> So can I ask, over
that-- you know, that time,

00:05:28.740 --> 00:05:32.430 align:middle line:84%
those four years, did
you find yourself relying

00:05:32.430 --> 00:05:34.890 align:middle line:84%
on anti-depressants
or medication?

00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:36.180 align:middle line:90%
Did you seek help?

00:05:36.180 --> 00:05:40.290 align:middle line:84%
>> No, I'm one of these people
who I'm very independent.

00:05:40.290 --> 00:05:41.680 align:middle line:90%
I just stay within myself.

00:05:41.680 --> 00:05:45.150 align:middle line:84%
I talked to my mom a
lot, and my mom helped me

00:05:45.150 --> 00:05:46.170 align:middle line:90%
through a lot of times.

00:05:46.170 --> 00:05:49.830 align:middle line:84%
And I got to a comfort
place, where I just wasn't

00:05:49.830 --> 00:05:51.000 align:middle line:90%
a successful person anymore.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:52.417 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought,
you know what?

00:05:52.417 --> 00:05:54.130 align:middle line:84%
Maybe this is as
good as it gets.

00:05:54.130 --> 00:05:56.130 align:middle line:84%
And so I just lived
every day with,

00:05:56.130 --> 00:05:59.220 align:middle line:84%
you know, wake up, do what
I do, look after my kid,

00:05:59.220 --> 00:06:02.040 align:middle line:84%
take him to school, bring him
home, and that was my life,

00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:06.990 align:middle line:84%
whereas before this happened,
I could conquer anything.

00:06:06.990 --> 00:06:10.585 align:middle line:84%
You know, I strived to
be somebody in my life

00:06:10.585 --> 00:06:12.210 align:middle line:84%
and make a bigger
impact in everything,

00:06:12.210 --> 00:06:13.043 align:middle line:90%
but I lost all that.

00:06:13.043 --> 00:06:14.280 align:middle line:90%
It was gone.

00:06:14.280 --> 00:06:18.000 align:middle line:84%
So I just sat there
and did nothing really.

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:20.706 align:middle line:84%
>> So you described
to me before--

00:06:20.706 --> 00:06:23.820 align:middle line:84%
before we started chatting,
you were saying to me

00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:26.940 align:middle line:84%
that that four-year period,
as you described it,

00:06:26.940 --> 00:06:31.490 align:middle line:84%
was Groundhog Day, and also a
feeling of complete numbness

00:06:31.490 --> 00:06:33.540 align:middle line:84%
that you just-- you
know, you really

00:06:33.540 --> 00:06:40.080 align:middle line:84%
couldn't feel any real emotion
or motivation to do anything.

00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:43.800 align:middle line:84%
And did you realize at the
time that you were depressed?

00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:48.330 align:middle line:84%
>> No, I didn't realize until
I looked back at that time.

00:06:48.330 --> 00:06:50.460 align:middle line:84%
My husband and I went
through a really bad time,

00:06:50.460 --> 00:06:52.980 align:middle line:90%
where I was just angry.

00:06:52.980 --> 00:06:56.050 align:middle line:84%
And I was angry that I
made the wrong decision,

00:06:56.050 --> 00:06:59.220 align:middle line:84%
and I was angry that
we were stuck here.

00:06:59.220 --> 00:07:02.100 align:middle line:84%
And so it caused a
lot of angst at home,

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:05.220 align:middle line:84%
