that it wasn't even him.

00:07:05.220 --> 00:07:07.410 align:middle line:90%
It was just me imploding.

00:07:07.410 --> 00:07:11.160 align:middle line:84%
You know, I was just sitting
there going, well, great,

00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:13.320 align:middle line:90%
this is Pam Brossman's life.

00:07:13.320 --> 00:07:16.330 align:middle line:84%
Is this all I'm going
to amount to in life?

00:07:16.330 --> 00:07:17.980 align:middle line:90%
And I just was miserable.

00:07:17.980 --> 00:07:23.100 align:middle line:84%
I was unhappy, so much so that
I was just walking around.

00:07:23.100 --> 00:07:25.003 align:middle line:90%
As you said, I was numb.

00:07:25.003 --> 00:07:25.920 align:middle line:90%
I didn't really just--

00:07:25.920 --> 00:07:27.690 align:middle line:90%
I just existed.

00:07:27.690 --> 00:07:33.990 align:middle line:84%
>> So in that numbness, did you
did you also find that you felt

00:07:33.990 --> 00:07:37.650 align:middle line:84%
a little bit of the victim
and self-pity, you know,

00:07:37.650 --> 00:07:40.440 align:middle line:90%
because in that place--

00:07:40.440 --> 00:07:43.510 align:middle line:84%
and it's so hard to pick
yourself out of it--

00:07:43.510 --> 00:07:45.630 align:middle line:84%
you sit in a place of
just blaming yourself

00:07:45.630 --> 00:07:48.720 align:middle line:84%
and those around you
and the situation.

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:50.580 align:middle line:90%
Was that true for you?

00:07:50.580 --> 00:07:52.065 align:middle line:90%
>> I-- Jo, I was angry.

00:07:52.065 --> 00:07:54.720 align:middle line:90%


00:07:54.720 --> 00:08:00.900 align:middle line:84%
I blamed somebody else for the
situation for those four years.

00:08:00.900 --> 00:08:05.670 align:middle line:84%
And I used that anger
to stay where I was.

00:08:05.670 --> 00:08:08.730 align:middle line:84%
And then one day, I
realized that if I

00:08:08.730 --> 00:08:11.400 align:middle line:84%
don't take responsibility
for making that decision that

00:08:11.400 --> 00:08:13.890 align:middle line:84%
put me in this
place, then I'm not

00:08:13.890 --> 00:08:16.390 align:middle line:84%
going to get out
of this hellhole.

00:08:16.390 --> 00:08:19.420 align:middle line:84%
And so I then had to
take responsibility

00:08:19.420 --> 00:08:22.840 align:middle line:84%
for, I made a mistake, and
then one day, my mom said

00:08:22.840 --> 00:08:27.250 align:middle line:84%
to me on the phone-- she said,
Pam, you got to the top once.

00:08:27.250 --> 00:08:29.580 align:middle line:90%
You can do it again.

00:08:29.580 --> 00:08:30.960 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, you know what?

00:08:30.960 --> 00:08:33.419 align:middle line:90%
My son deserves a better life.

00:08:33.419 --> 00:08:35.100 align:middle line:90%
She's right.

00:08:35.100 --> 00:08:37.086 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I flicked
my switch back on.

00:08:37.086 --> 00:08:39.419 align:middle line:84%
>> So was that-- that was the
light bulb moment for you.

00:08:39.419 --> 00:08:41.340 align:middle line:90%
>> That was it for me.

00:08:41.340 --> 00:08:45.210 align:middle line:84%
My son came home crying one
day, and he just looked at me

00:08:45.210 --> 00:08:49.050 align:middle line:84%
and said, Mommy, I want children
to be able to play with me.

00:08:49.050 --> 00:08:51.060 align:middle line:90%
Why can't I bring them home?

00:08:51.060 --> 00:08:55.590 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought,
this hole that I'm in,

00:08:55.590 --> 00:08:58.080 align:middle line:84%
how can I inspire
my own son to be

00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:01.740 align:middle line:84%
the best person he can be in
life when his mom's given up?

00:09:01.740 --> 00:09:03.700 align:middle line:84%
And I did it for the
love of my child.

00:09:03.700 --> 00:09:04.500 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:09:04.500 --> 00:09:04.980 align:middle line:90%
>>I did it.

00:09:04.980 --> 00:09:05.813 align:middle line:90%
>> I did it for him.

00:09:05.813 --> 00:09:08.620 align:middle line:90%


00:09:08.620 --> 00:09:11.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Take a breath.

00:09:11.060 --> 00:09:12.483 align:middle line:90%
It takes courage.

00:09:12.483 --> 00:09:13.400 align:middle line:90%
It takes real courage.

00:09:13.400 --> 00:09:15.550 align:middle line:90%
>> I just go back in time.

00:09:15.550 --> 00:09:19.320 align:middle line:84%
It was a really, really
sad time in my life.

00:09:19.320 --> 00:09:23.670 align:middle line:84%
>> So in that time leading
up to that light bulb moment,

00:09:23.670 --> 00:09:25.320 align:middle line:90%
where everything changed--

00:09:25.320 --> 00:09:26.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:09:26.750 --> 00:09:30.020 align:middle line:84%
>> --do you have any day to
day tools that helped you get

00:09:30.020 --> 00:09:33.710 align:middle line:84%
through, or literally until that
light bulb moment that almost,

00:09:33.710 --> 00:09:37.690 align:middle line:90%
you know, slap, the--

00:09:37.690 --> 00:09:39.730 align:middle line:84%
were beautiful words
from your mother.

00:09:39.730 --> 00:09:40.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:43.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Were you-- what were your
coping strategies up until that

00:09:43.690 --> 00:09:44.490 align:middle line:90%
point?

00:09:44.490 --> 00:09:46.540 align:middle line:84%
Or you feel you didn't
really have any,

00:09:46.540 --> 00:09:47.980 align:middle line:90%
that you were just existing?

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:49.300 align:middle line:90%
>> I wasn't--

00:09:49.300 --> 00:09:50.800 align:middle line:90%
I didn't have any skills.

00:09:50.800 --> 00:09:55.690 align:middle line:84%
All I was doing was my
husband was providing for us,

00:09:55.690 --> 00:10:00.160 align:middle line:84%
even though he was miserable,
and I was providing for my son.

00:10:00.160 --> 00:10:01.525 align:middle line:90%
That was it.

00:10:01.525 --> 00:10:03.400 align:middle line:84%
I didn't do anything
outside my comfort zone.

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:04.442 align:middle line:90%
I didn't spend any money.

00:10:04.442 --> 00:10:08.380 align:middle line:84%
Every cent that my
husband made, I just

00:10:08.380 --> 00:10:10.270 align:middle line:84%
kept it towards
paying the bills.

00:10:10.270 --> 00:10:14.210 align:middle line:84%
So there was no coping, because
I didn't know how to cope.

00:10:14.210 --> 00:10:17.110 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so then
with the, you know,

00:10:17.110 --> 00:10:22.030 align:middle line:84%
changing of the tides and the
inspirational words of wisdom

00:10:22.030 --> 00:10:25.270 align:middle line:84%
from your mom, what, then--
what was the transition?

00:10:25.270 --> 00:10:29.050 align:middle line:84%
What kind of tools did you
start to go out and seek

00:10:29.050 --> 00:10:31.810 align:middle line:84%
that helped you put
yourself out of that rut?

00:10:31.810 --> 00:10:36.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the first thing
I said to my husband,

00:10:36.020 --> 00:10:38.350 align:middle line:84%
he came home from work one
day after I spoke to my mom,

00:10:38.350 --> 00:10:40.480 align:middle line:84%
and I just said, this isn't
the life I want for me,

00:10:40.480 --> 00:10:43.270 align:middle line:84%
and this is not the
life I want for my son.

00:10:43.270 --> 00:10:46.180 align:middle line:84%
We did have a little bit
of money in the unit,

00:10:46.180 --> 00:10:47.620 align:middle line:90%
because we bought the unit.

00:10:47.620 --> 00:10:49.680 align:middle line:84%
But we pretty much--
the bank owned the unit.

00:10:49.680 --> 00:10:51.200 align:middle line:90%
We didn't have much in it.

00:10:51.200 --> 00:10:54.410 align:middle line:84%
But I said, with what we've
got left in this unit, I said,

00:10:54.410 --> 00:10:56.440 align:middle line:90%
I want you to be happy.

00:10:56.440 --> 00:11:04.940 align:middle line:84%
So I-- we agreed to sell
it, and we rented it back.

00:11:04.940 --> 00:11:09.510 align:middle line:84%
And he quit his job, and
in that moment, we decided,

00:11:09.510 --> 00:11:10.820 align:middle line:90%
you know what?

00:11:10.820 --> 00:11:13.670 align:middle line:84%
We're going to get back out
there and do what we do best,

00:11:13.670 --> 00:11:17.390 align:middle line:84%
and that's Pam and Steve
Brossman success story.

00:11:17.390 --> 00:11:19.970 align:middle line:84%
So we took a little
bit of that money,

00:11:19.970 --> 00:11:22.940 align:middle line:90%
and we invested it in us.

00:11:22.940 --> 00:11:25.730 align:middle line:84%
And we went on a
millionaire cruise

00:11:25.730 --> 00:11:29.720 align:middle line:84%
with 100 other millionaire
mindset people.

00:11:29.720 --> 00:11:33.827 align:middle line:84%
And that was a game
changer for us.

00:11:33.827 --> 00:11:35.410 align:middle line:84%
And so that's when
everything changed.

00:11:35.410 --> 00:11:37.150 align:middle line:90%
It was like, you know what?

00:11:37.150 --> 00:11:38.800 align:middle line:90%
Mom's right.

00:11:38.800 --> 00:11:40.940 align:middle line:84%
I can get back out
there and do it again.

00:11:40.940 --> 00:11:45.220 align:middle line:84%
So I took responsibility
for it, and then I

00:11:45.220 --> 00:11:47.780 align:middle line:90%
decided it was time to change.

00:11:47.780 --> 00:11:52.610 align:middle line:84%
And in that moment,
everything changed.

00:11:52.610 --> 00:11:53.600 align:middle line:90%
>> So over the--

00:11:53.600 --> 00:11:57.170 align:middle line:84%
you know, over those
changing landscape,

00:11:57.170 --> 00:12:00.480 align:middle line:84%
you know, from going on the
cruise to a whole change

00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:02.540 align:middle line:84%
in mindset, which I want
to come to in a moment,

00:12:02.540 --> 00:12:07.340 align:middle line:84%
because, you know, this is a
big subject around the capacity

00:12:07.340 --> 00:12:11.000 align:middle line:84%
to really use our minds
and direct our focus

00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:14.300 align:middle line:84%
to create the reality
that we want to create.

00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:16.980 align:middle line:84%
But there's also
healing along the way.

00:12:16.980 --> 00:12:17.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:12:17.780 --> 00:12:20.960 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, emotional healing
along the way for what's been

00:12:20.960 --> 00:12:23.310 align:middle line:90%
experienced and what comes up.

00:12:23.310 --> 00:12:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And you mentioned before that
there was a lot of anger,

00:12:25.760 --> 00:12:28.160 align:middle line:84%
a lot of guilt,
and a lot of shame.

00:12:28.160 --> 00:12:32.450 align:middle line:84%
Can you share with us how you've
managed, just for yourself--

00:12:32.450 --> 00:12:35.030 align:middle line:84%
because everyone's
different-- but how have you

00:12:35.030 --> 00:12:38.750 align:middle line:84%
managed to make peace with
those thoughts and feelings?

00:12:38.750 --> 00:12:41.390 align:middle line:84%
>> There was somebody who was
involved in the fact that we

00:12:41.390 --> 00:12:42.800 align:middle line:90%
lost our home.

00:12:42.800 --> 00:12:47.790 align:middle line:84%
And he happened to live
a couple of streets away.

00:12:47.790 --> 00:12:52.700 align:middle line:84%
And for those four years, I
used to see him every day.

00:12:52.700 --> 00:12:57.490 align:middle line:84%
And when I saw him, I
felt sick, because he just

00:12:57.490 --> 00:13:01.270 align:middle line:84%
represented what he put me and
my child and my family through.

00:13:01.270 --> 00:13:04.960 align:middle line:84%
So I did blame him, and
I used to get the shakes.

00:13:04.960 --> 00:13:08.980 align:middle line:84%
I felt physically
not coping, and then

00:13:08.980 --> 00:13:12.520 align:middle line:84%
when we made that decision that
I had to take responsibility

00:13:12.520 --> 00:13:18.350 align:middle line:84%
for what had happened, I
started seeing him and smiling.

00:13:18.350 --> 00:13:20.540 align:middle line:84%
And then I realized
that until I let

00:13:20.540 --> 00:13:24.770 align:middle line:84%
it go and let go of
the blame, my world

00:13:24.770 --> 00:13:27.140 align:middle line:90%
is not going to change.

00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:30.710 align:middle line:84%
It was the hardest thing
I've ever had to do,

00:13:30.710 --> 00:13:35.670 align:middle line:84%
but when I did that,
I could let it go.

00:13:35.670 --> 00:13:36.950 align:middle line:90%
And all these doors opened.

00:13:36.950 --> 00:13:39.690 align:middle line:84%
It was like the
darkness had lifted.

00:13:39.690 --> 00:13:42.715 align:middle line:84%
>> So what I'm hearing almost
is like the power of forgiveness

00:13:42.715 --> 00:13:43.515 align:middle line:90%
towards this man--

00:13:43.515 --> 00:13:43.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:13:43.830 --> 00:13:44.310 align:middle line:90%
Yep.

00:13:44.310 --> 00:13:45.370 align:middle line:90%
>> --released you.

00:13:45.370 --> 00:13:47.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep, without a doubt.

00:13:47.790 --> 00:13:52.720 align:middle line:84%
The hatred that I had for
him was just killing my soul.

00:13:52.720 --> 00:13:55.690 align:middle line:84%
It was no-- I had never
experienced as much hatred

00:13:55.690 --> 00:14:02.170 align:middle line:84%
as I had to this one person for
putting my family through this.

00:14:02.170 --> 00:14:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And then I started
reading some books

00:14:05.400 --> 00:14:09.030 align:middle line:84%
and realizing that,
you know what?

00:14:09.030 --> 00:14:13.560 align:middle line:84%
I made the ultimate decision
to go ahead with it.

00:14:13.560 --> 00:14:17.060 align:middle line:90%
He just gave me the opportunity.

00:14:17.060 --> 00:14:19.510 align:middle line:84%
And then when I took
responsibility for it

00:14:19.510 --> 00:14:24.880 align:middle line:84%
and let him go, then doors
started opening for us.

00:14:24.880 --> 00:14:28.930 align:middle line:90%
And we got success so fast.

00:14:28.930 --> 00:14:30.800 align:middle line:90%
It was crazy.

00:14:30.800 --> 00:14:32.555 align:middle line:90%
So really, I had to let it go.

00:14:32.555 --> 00:14:33.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:33.740 --> 00:14:36.965 align:middle line:84%
So in the letting go, there was
also a shift in your mindset.

00:14:36.965 --> 00:14:38.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:14:38.270 --> 00:14:41.780 align:middle line:84%
>> And so did you have--
were there any sort of daily

00:14:41.780 --> 00:14:45.890 align:middle line:84%
practices that once you started
to realize and become mindful

00:14:45.890 --> 00:14:50.330 align:middle line:84%
that it was very much about
what you focused on and how you

00:14:50.330 --> 00:14:54.710 align:middle line:84%
focused on it, that changed
the flow of energy and what you

00:14:54.710 --> 00:14:57.200 align:middle line:90%
could attract into your life?

00:14:57.200 --> 00:14:59.900 align:middle line:84%
Did you have daily
practices in that respect

00:14:59.900 --> 00:15:01.460 align:middle line:90%
to keep you focused?

00:15:01.460 --> 00:15:04.790 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm the sort of person who
doesn't like to have debt.

00:15:04.790 --> 00:15:09.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm really good with money,
which is why this floored me.

00:15:09.380 --> 00:15:12.410 align:middle line:84%
And so we had this
$30k debt that we

00:15:12.410 --> 00:15:16.250 align:middle line:84%
incurred having to get ourselves
out of this financial mess.

00:15:16.250 --> 00:15:17.458 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, you know what?

00:15:17.458 --> 00:15:19.083 align:middle line:84%
I don't want this
hanging over my head,

00:15:19.083 --> 00:15:21.080 align:middle line:84%
because this is what
gets people in trouble.

00:15:21.080 --> 00:15:25.760 align:middle line:84%
They took forever just
paying off the interest.

00:15:25.760 --> 00:15:28.130 align:middle line:90%
So I went in search--

00:15:28.130 --> 00:15:31.340 align:middle line:84%
being the solution person, I
went in search for a solution.

00:15:31.340 --> 00:15:35.420 align:middle line:84%
And I found a way to
get rid of that 30k debt

00:15:35.420 --> 00:15:38.120 align:middle line:90%
interest-free in six months.

00:15:38.120 --> 00:15:41.330 align:middle line:84%
And that was an
achievement for me.

00:15:41.330 --> 00:15:44.420 align:middle line:84%
And then I just saw all these
people in the same position

00:15:44.420 --> 00:15:50.300 align:middle line:84%
as me financially struggling,
and I just thought,

00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:52.650 align:middle line:90%
I can help these people.

00:15:52.650 --> 00:15:59.340 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to get out there,
specifically women, help them

00:15:59.340 --> 00:16:02.730 align:middle line:84%
if they got themselves
into a financial mess.

00:16:02.730 --> 00:16:04.080 align:middle line:90%
And that inspired me.

00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:06.690 align:middle line:84%
And when I had that energy
that it was no longer about me,

00:16:06.690 --> 00:16:09.300 align:middle line:84%
it was about helping
other people overcome

00:16:09.300 --> 00:16:13.960 align:middle line:84%
what I'd just been through,
that was a huge shift for me.

00:16:13.960 --> 00:16:17.580 align:middle line:84%
>> So it's like you found an
even greater motive bigger than

00:16:17.580 --> 00:16:18.380 align:middle line:90%
yourself.

00:16:18.380 --> 00:16:19.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:19.370 --> 00:16:20.170 align:middle line:90%
Yep.

00:16:20.170 --> 00:16:25.340 align:middle line:84%
>> And a real purpose to connect
to and to give you some meaning

00:16:25.340 --> 00:16:26.140 align:middle line:90%
and purpose.

00:16:26.140 --> 00:16:31.342 align:middle line:84%
And that became your drive to
continue to bring you back up.

00:16:31.342 --> 00:16:32.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, because
what happened, Jo,

00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:36.050 align:middle line:84%
is I never told
anybody what happened.

00:16:36.050 --> 00:16:38.830 align:middle line:90%
It was like that secret.

00:16:38.830 --> 00:16:42.220 align:middle line:84%
And as we started becoming
more and more successful,

00:16:42.220 --> 00:16:45.580 align:middle line:84%
I swept it further and
further under the carpet.

00:16:45.580 --> 00:16:48.640 align:middle line:84%
I thought, what impact will
this have on me and my business

00:16:48.640 --> 00:16:52.420 align:middle line:84%
my brand if people
know of my failure?

00:16:52.420 --> 00:16:56.050 align:middle line:84%
So I just let people believe
I was this successful woman

00:16:56.050 --> 00:16:58.330 align:middle line:90%
all along.

00:16:58.330 --> 00:17:01.570 align:middle line:84%
And then-- but I felt
like I was living a lie.

00:17:01.570 --> 00:17:05.170 align:middle line:84%
It was eating at me,
because I'm a very--

00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:08.777 align:middle line:84%
integrity and truth is
really important to me.

00:17:08.777 --> 00:17:10.569 align:middle line:84%
And then one day at an
event I was running,

00:17:10.569 --> 00:17:13.420 align:middle line:84%
a woman came up to me, and
I was on stage presenting.

00:17:13.420 --> 00:17:15.920 align:middle line:84%
And in the break, she came up
to me, and she started crying.

00:17:15.920 --> 00:17:17.619 align:middle line:84%
And I asked her
why she was crying,

00:17:17.619 --> 00:17:20.760 align:middle line:84%
and she said to me, Pam, I
just want to be like you.

00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:22.750 align:middle line:84%
You know, you've been
successful all your life.

00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:25.740 align:middle line:84%
And in that moment,
I just thought,

00:17:25.740 --> 00:17:27.845 align:middle line:90%
I can't hide this anymore.

00:17:27.845 --> 00:17:29.970 align:middle line:84%
You know, these women are
putting me on a pedestal,

00:17:29.970 --> 00:17:33.180 align:middle line:90%
when two years ago, I was them.

00:17:33.180 --> 00:17:35.942 align:middle line:84%
And that was a huge
shift for me just

00:17:35.942 --> 00:17:37.650 align:middle line:84%
wanting to help people
and say, you know,

00:17:37.650 --> 00:17:40.980 align:middle line:90%
anybody can flick the switch.

00:17:40.980 --> 00:17:46.170 align:middle line:84%
Don't spend four years
like I did figuring it out.

00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:50.220 align:middle line:84%
>> And then the fact that you
became open and vulnerable

00:17:50.220 --> 00:17:53.370 align:middle line:84%
and shared your story,
how did you then find that

00:17:53.370 --> 00:17:57.360 align:middle line:84%
that's impacted your career
and your ability to connect

00:17:57.360 --> 00:17:58.980 align:middle line:90%
and engage with people?

00:17:58.980 --> 00:17:59.910 align:middle line:90%
>> I created a--

00:17:59.910 --> 00:18:02.490 align:middle line:84%
I wrote a book about
what happened to me,

00:18:02.490 --> 00:18:04.830 align:middle line:90%
and I created a movie about it.

00:18:04.830 --> 00:18:07.110 align:middle line:84%
It was kind of like
this situation here.

00:18:07.110 --> 00:18:10.830 align:middle line:84%
I had a film for the
launch of the book,

00:18:10.830 --> 00:18:14.250 align:middle line:90%
and I cried in that story.

00:18:14.250 --> 00:18:16.330 align:middle line:84%
I was reliving it
like I cried before.

00:18:16.330 --> 00:18:18.550 align:middle line:90%
It's just so real for me.

00:18:18.550 --> 00:18:21.800 align:middle line:84%
And I was hesitant
about putting that out.

00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:23.730 align:middle line:84%
I thought, should I
just tell it in the book

00:18:23.730 --> 00:18:26.700 align:middle line:84%
and not get real
and raw about it?

00:18:26.700 --> 00:18:30.700 align:middle line:84%
And the producer said to me,
no, Pam, that's the story.

00:18:30.700 --> 00:18:33.270 align:middle line:90%
You've got to put it out.

00:18:33.270 --> 00:18:38.070 align:middle line:84%
And the feedback that I had from
women from seeing that video

00:18:38.070 --> 00:18:40.500 align:middle line:84%
and saying, Pam, you
know, you changed my life.

00:18:40.500 --> 00:18:45.210 align:middle line:84%
You made me realize that
it's OK to fall down,

00:18:45.210 --> 00:18:47.620 align:middle line:90%
and you can get back up again.

00:18:47.620 --> 00:18:51.780 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, it really
was a life-changing

00:18:51.780 --> 00:18:55.080 align:middle line:84%
and put me on the path that
I'm on now, which is awesome.

00:18:55.080 --> 00:18:59.260 align:middle line:84%
I love it, changing women's
lives for the better.

00:18:59.260 --> 00:19:04.470 align:middle line:84%
>> So if-- can we go just back
for a second when you spoke

00:19:04.470 --> 00:19:09.300 align:middle line:84%
about using money and getting
out of debt as a motivator?

00:19:09.300 --> 00:19:10.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:19:10.110 --> 00:19:12.330 align:middle line:84%
>> So obviously,
through your experience,

00:19:12.330 --> 00:19:15.480 align:middle line:84%
you've had an enormous amount
of anxiety that would have come

00:19:15.480 --> 00:19:18.280 align:middle line:84%
out of the financial loss
that you went through.

00:19:18.280 --> 00:19:19.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:19:19.080 --> 00:19:21.990 align:middle line:84%
>> And then you formed a
strategy to actually get

00:19:21.990 --> 00:19:22.900 align:middle line:90%
yourself out of debt.

00:19:22.900 --> 00:19:23.700 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:23.700 --> 00:19:26.360 align:middle line:84%
>> So along the way,
you know, if we have,

00:19:26.360 --> 00:19:28.290 align:middle line:84%
in our audience
today, listening,

00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:33.120 align:middle line:84%
people who are either in
a position of depression

00:19:33.120 --> 00:19:36.450 align:middle line:84%
or anxiety because of
their financial situation,

00:19:36.450 --> 00:19:39.300 align:middle line:84%
what kind of tips and tools
could you start directing them

00:19:39.300 --> 00:19:42.640 align:middle line:84%
in to help manage that
situation for themselves?

00:19:42.640 --> 00:19:46.080 align:middle line:84%
>> You have to give
yourself small quick wins.

00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:49.080 align:middle line:84%
You have to work
your way back up,

00:19:49.080 --> 00:19:52.130 align:middle line:84%
and I just kept stretching
myself a little bit more

00:19:52.130 --> 00:19:53.190 align:middle line:90%
and a little bit more.

00:19:53.190 --> 00:19:55.630 align:middle line:90%
So I'll give you an example.

00:19:55.630 --> 00:19:57.840 align:middle line:84%
I promised my child that
he could have a puppy when

00:19:57.840 --> 00:19:59.730 align:middle line:90%
he was six years old, and--

00:19:59.730 --> 00:20:01.650 align:middle line:84%
actually, it was
when he was five.

00:20:01.650 --> 00:20:04.440 align:middle line:84%
And I broke that promise,
and I didn't like that.

00:20:04.440 --> 00:20:07.857 align:middle line:84%
And so I said to my husband,
Hunter's a six years old,

00:20:07.857 --> 00:20:09.940 align:middle line:84%
and this is after we'd
been on the mindset cruise.

00:20:09.940 --> 00:20:12.120 align:middle line:90%
So we'd shifted.

00:20:12.120 --> 00:20:15.240 align:middle line:84%
And I said, it's time
for him to have a yard,

00:20:15.240 --> 00:20:17.430 align:middle line:84%
and it's time for us
to move into a house.

00:20:17.430 --> 00:20:22.390 align:middle line:84%
But we were paying a rent that
was so comfortable for us.

00:20:22.390 --> 00:20:26.080 align:middle line:84%
And once again, we had to
get over that mindset of,

00:20:26.080 --> 00:20:28.200 align:middle line:90%
we're comfortable now.

00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:30.590 align:middle line:90%
Shall we just stay here?

00:20:30.590 --> 00:20:33.320 align:middle line:84%
And I said to Steve,
we're not stretching.

00:20:33.320 --> 00:20:37.570 align:middle line:84%
So we found a house that
was four times what we were

00:20:37.570 --> 00:20:40.122 align:middle line:90%
paying where we were living.

00:20:40.122 --> 00:20:41.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Wow, that's
stretching yourself.

00:20:41.580 --> 00:20:44.470 align:middle line:90%
>> That was a huge stretch.

00:20:44.470 --> 00:20:46.720 align:middle line:84%
But I said to Steve-- we
went-- walked down there,

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:48.262 align:middle line:84%
